The paper proposes a new layer for synthesizing photorealistic images given an input semantic layout. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The proposed method involves a learned transformation, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. The paper also mentions experiments on several challenging datasets, which may indicate the involvement of graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) subcategories.
